approve(address,uint256).details: Sets `account` as the approved account to manage token `id`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist. - The caller must be the owner of the token,   or an approved operator for the token owner. Emits an {Approval} event.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the number of tokens owned by `owner`. Requirements: - `owner` must not be the zero address.

params._dpFee: Address of the fee strategy contract
params._optionPricing: Address of the option pricing contract

getApproved(uint256).details: Returns the account approved to manage token `id`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist.

params.isPut: Whether the option is a put

params._tick: The tick to get the price for

returns._0: uint256 The price per call asset

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Returns whether `operator` is approved to manage the tokens of `owner`.

multicall(bytes[]).details: Receives and executes a batch of function calls on this contract.

returns._0: string The name of the contract

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the owner of token `id`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Transfers token `id` from `from` to `to`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist. - `from` must be the owner of the token. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - The caller must be the owner of the token, or be approved to manage the token. - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement   {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon a safe transfer. Emits a {Transfer} event.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Sets whether `operator` is approved to manage the tokens of the caller. Emits an {ApprovalForAll} event.

returns.ac: The assets cache containing settlement results

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165 This function call must use less than 30000 gas.

returns._0: string The symbol of the contract

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers token `id` from `from` to `to`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist. - `from` must be the owner of the token. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - The caller must be the owner of the token, or be approved to manage the token. Emits a {Transfer} event.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

approvedPools(address).notice: Mapping of pool address to approval status

approvedTTLs(uint256).notice: Mapping of TTL to approval status

exerciseDelegator(address,address).notice: Mapping of owner to delegate to exercise status

getFee(uint256,uint256).notice: Gets the fee for a given amount and premium

getPremiumAmount(address,bool,uint256,ui.notice: Gets the premium amount for an option

getPricePerCallAssetViaTick(address,int2.notice: Gets the price per call asset via a specific tick

name().notice: Returns the name of the contract

opData(uint256).notice: Mapping of option ID to option data

opTickMap(uint256,uint256).notice: Mapping of option ID to option ticks

positionSplitter((uint256,address,uint25.notice: Splits a position into a new option

settlers(address).notice: Mapping of settler address to approval status

symbol().notice: Returns the symbol of the contract

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Returns the token URI for a given token ID

tokenURIFetcher().notice: Address of the token URI fetcher

updateExerciseDelegate(address,bool).notice: Updates the exercise delegate for the caller
